post_text: On Monday, May 18th from 8-1 you may stop by your students building to pick up their items from school and drop off any library books, text books or technology that you've borrowed from the school at that time. This will be a drive through system. You will notify the staff in the parking lot who your student is and hand them any items that need turned in and they will get your students items from inside the building. We already have everything bagged up for each student so that nobody will need to enter the building. We will also be giving out bags of fruit that day to everyone at Grand Ave., so if you have students at the Impact Center you can swing over to Grand Ave. and grab a bag of fruit if you would like. We will also be serving ToGo lunches that day for the week from 11-12:30. If you have any questions give us a call!

shared_text:
Heir Force Community School
April 29, 2019 at 12:14 PM ¬∑

We are excited that we are just two weeks away from our annual Spring concert! The kids are looking forward to performing for you that night! They will be performing again in the sanctuary of Cornerstone Church located at 2000 N. Cole St. on Friday, May 10th at 6:30 PM, please have them arrive by 6 pm so they have enough time to use the restroom and meet up with their class! For this concert we are asking that all students wear dark colored pants or skirts with bright colored polos or shirts...girls are also welcome to wear spring dresses. Tickets are now on sale for this event in both of our school office locations. Tickets are still just $3 in advance or $5 at the door, students who are not in the performance are $2. As a reminder, ticket sales help to offset costs for all field trips and other fun parties throughout the year! We appreciate your support ‚ù§Ô∏è
